	abstract = {Which variables provide independent information about the cross-section of future returns? Portfolio sorts and Fama-{MacBeth} regressions cannot easily answer this question when the number of candidate variables is large and when cross-terms might be important. We introduce a new method based on ideas from the machine learning literature that can be used in this context. Applying the method to past-return-based prediction of future returns, short-term returns become the most important predictors. A trading strategy based on our findings has an information ratio twice as high as a Fama-{MacBeth} regression accounting for two-way interactions. Transaction costs do not explain the results.},
